<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1925-05-31T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1925-05-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="442" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d442">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">881.00/1053</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The French Ambassador</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Daeschner</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Translation<note n="7" xml:id="d442fn7">File translation revised.</note>]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1925-05-31"><hi rend="italic">May 31,
                                1925</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Mr. Secretary of State</hi>: In compliance with
                            instructions from my Government, I have the honor to inform Your
                            Excellency that the Statute of Tangier established through the Paris
                            agreement of December 18, 1923, will go into effect on June 1.</p>
                        <p>This step has been taken in accord with the Governments of Spain and
                            Great Britain, and my Government hopes that the Government of the United
                            States will welcome the establishment of a regime, to the arrangements
                            of which it has raised no fundamental objection.</p>
                        <p>Please accept [etc.]</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">E. Daeschner</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>